Java Assignment - Cinema Ticket Booking System
Objective
Write a Java program that simulates a simple cinema ticket booking system using functions,
arrays, loops, and conditional statements.
Program Requirements
The cinema has 5 rows and 6 seats per row.
Use:
char[][] seats = new char[5][6];
String[] movieNames = {"Superman","Avatar","Minecraft","Inside Out","F1"};
Initially all seats contain 'O' (Available). Booked seats contain 'X'.
User will enter seat number. Ex: 12 where “1” represents No. of row and “2” represents No.
of column
Main Menu
1. Display Seats
2. Book Seat
3. Cancel Booking
4. Show all movies.
5. Show number of available and booked seats
0. Exit

Features
• Display all.
• Book a seat after validating row and seat numbers.
• Cancel an existing booking.
• Display booked seats, available seats.
• Exit the program with a goodbye message.
Input Validation
Validate row numbers (1-5) and seat numbers (1-6). Display 'Invalid Seat.' for invalid input.
Bonus Challenges
• Take number of rows & columns that will represent the seats.
• Take number of movies and their names.
• Display 'Almost Full' when occupancy exceeds 80%.
